summary:
Peter Parker: Hey, Mr.Stark, you know how you called that ugly alien guy, Squidward?
Tony Stark: Yeah, Underoo’s. What about it?...
body:
Peter Parker: Hey, Mr.Stark, you know how you called that ugly alien guy, Squidward?

Tony Stark: Yeah, Underoo’s. What about it?

Peter Parker: You know who Plankton is right? Small, Green, and Evil?

(Clint getting interested in the conversation)

Tony Stark: Yeah, What about him?

Peter Parker: Oh nothing, just that Thanos brain is as small as Plankton.

Clint: and his nose

Peter Parker: and his Dic…

Tony Stark: Don’t finish that sentence or I’ll get Natasha on you.

summary: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse: A Review by J. Jonah Jameson.
body:
Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse: A Review by J. Jonah Jameson.

Longtime readers may be aware of my opinion on a certain so-called “hero”, making the content of this review not much of a surprise.

The film features not one, not two, but THREE Spider-Men, a Spider-Woman, a pig, and a robot. This film is nothing but PROPAGANDA designed to promote the menace otherwise known as Spider-Man.

In addition to showing support to a societal menace, the film also slanders law-abiding New Yorkers such as Wilson Fisk and Norman Osborn and the corporation Alchemax.

The film makers should be ashamed of themselves for producing such drivel. Zero stars.

title: Sequels & Spin-offs For Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse Are In The Works
body:
Sequels & spin-offs for #SpiderMan: #IntoTheSpiderVerse are in the works! #SpiderGwen #Silk #SpiderWoman

Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse has officially hit theaters and with critics scoring of 98% on Rotten Tomato a sequel is already in the works.  Amy Pascal, the producer of he film has plans for spinoffs as well but the sequel is where it’s at.  It is said that the sequel won’t focus only on Miles Morales but will mainly focus on Gwen Stacy aka Spider-Gwen.
